claim.claim-text:
1. A printing apparatus which comprises
an array of at least two printhead chips, an end portion of a first printhead chip overlapping an end portion of a second, consecutive printhead chip, each printhead chip including a plurality of ink ejection nozzles;
a sensing means that is operatively arranged with respect to the printhead chips to generate overlap data representing an extent of overlap of the end portions;
means for generating continuous tone print data for the array of printhead chips and an initial dither matrix to be applied to the continuous tone print data;
a summation means for applying the overlap data to the initial dither matrix to generate an output value; and
processing means for applying the output value to the continuous tone print data.
